Patient: Is it safe for me to exercise with my heart condition?
Healthcare Educator: Yes, it's safe. Exercise can strengthen your heart and improve your health. 

Patient: What kind of exercises can I do?
Healthcare Educator: Walking, swimming or cycling. Start slow and gradually increase time and intensity.

Patient: My neighborhood isn't safe for outdoor activities. What can I do?
Healthcare Educator: Indoor activities work too. Try stationary cycling or exercise videos at home.

Patient: Will exercise tire me out?
Healthcare Educator: You may feel tired initially. With time, your energy should improve.

Patient: How often should I exercise?
Healthcare Educator: Aim for 30 minutes a day, five days a week. Start slow and build up.